<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--FerrySinking     10-17 0134</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Ferry Sinking,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>17 Drown In Ferry Sinking</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 17 people drowned when a
small ferry boat sank off Luzon island on the same day that 55
people were killed in a similar sinking in the central Philippines,
the Philippine Constabulary reported today.
   A belated report said five other people were missing from the
Lady Aurea, a motorized outrigger which capsized as it was buffeted
by big waves Friday off Aurora province, 120 miles northeast of
Manila. It said 11 others were rescued.
   The report gave no other details.
   At least 55 people drowned and 77 others were rescued when an
overloaded ferry boat sank during a squall Friday as it was sailing
from Samar to Leyte island in the central Philippines, the Coast
Guard reported last Saturday.
</TEXT>
