<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--South Street Attacks,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Youths Attack and Rob Several on South Street Following Anti-Drug
Concert</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gangs of youths surged through the city's
popular South Street area following an anti-drug rap concert,
robbing and beating people, said police, who arrested 13.
   A firefighter trying to help a woman attacked by a gang suffered
a broken nose, said Detective William Brennan. He said a youth was
arrested for the beating, which occurred Saturday afternoon.
   About three hours later, a gang beat and robbed another woman
then got away, Brennan said.
   Shortly afterward, a gang broke a store window and removed
jackets and other clothing. The youths were chased by witnesses,
and police arrested eight suspects, Brennan said.
   A short time later, four people were arrested on charges of
beating and robbing a man eight blocks from the store, Brennan said.
   Brennan said police did not have an estimate of the number of
youths involved in the attacks, but several small groups had roamed
the area.
</TEXT>
