Mount Makalu I, but one of them fell and disappeared while
descending the world's fifth tallest mountain, the Tourism Ministry
said today.
   The ministry said Tomasz Kopys, 35, an electrical engineer, and
Ryszark Kolakowski, 34, a building engineer, both from Warsaw,
reached the summit of the 27,758-foot Himalayan peak on Friday, and
Kolakowski slipped on the mountain and disappeared while they were
descending.
   Kopys reported he searched for Kolakowski but could not find him
because of bad weather, the ministry said.
