<HEAD>Student Dies After Crashing Through Skylight</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Rabsary is cq</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HIALEAH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 16-year-old girl who crashed through a
skylight while taking yearbook pictures on the roof of her high
school has died after two days in a coma, authorities said.
   Rabsary Gutierrez, a junior at Hialeah-Miami Lakes High, dropped
30 feet on Friday when she apparently misjudged her step and
plunged through the glass skylight onto a concrete stairway,
suffering head, brain and lung injuries.
   She never regained consciousness and died Sunday at Jackson
Memorial Hospital, said Principal Bill Noble.
   ``She was a real sweet person whom everybody cared about,'' he
said. ``This has been real difficult for all of us who knew her.''
   Special counselors came to the school today to help students
deal with the tragedy, he said.
   Miss Gutierrez had just taken a picture on top of the
three-story building when she tried to step over the skylight.
Instead, she crashed through as a teacher and 24 students looked
on, police Lt. Lowell Coffin said.
   The students had been warned to walk around the skylight, and
students had gone on the roof previously to take pictures without
incident, officials said.
