<HEAD>Duarte Returns From Medical Treatment in Washington</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Jose Napoleon Duarte
has returned from Washington, where he received his fourth
chemotherapy treatment for liver cancer.
   Duarte, 62, planned to work in his office Monday but no public
appearances were scheduled, government sources said. He returned
Sunday on a commercial flight.
   During the seven-day stay at Walter Reed Army Medical Center,
Duarte also underwent examinations to determine the results of the
previous treatment.
   Part of his stomach was removed at Walter Reed in June and
doctors said the cancer had spread to his liver. He was given six
to 18 months to live.
   His Salvadoran doctor, Jose Luis Saca, said recently that
Duarte's health has improved.
