<HEAD>Environmental Lobby Denounces Bush Record</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small group of environmental activists gathered
outside George Bush's Massachusetts campaign office Monday,
denouncing the Republican presidential candidate's environmental
record and calling him a hypocrite for bad-mouthing Michael
Dukakis' role in Boston Harbor pollution.
   The group released a report compiled by a national environmental
lobby that said Bush, as vice president, took or endorsed numerous
steps that have harmed or endangered the nation's waters and
wetlands.
