task force that rescinded or relaxed several regulations affecting
sewage treatment and wetlands protection programs.
   The group also credited Dukakis with beginning the cleanup of
Boston Harbor despite cutbacks in federal cleanup funds because of
Reagan administration cuts endorsed by Bush.
