<HEAD>President Lauds Virtue of Combining Religion with ABCs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan on Monday praised Roman
Catholic schools for teaching young people spiritual values as well
as the educational basics.
   Addressing students of two parochial high schools in northeast
Washington, Reagan said ``it amazes me that while you are exploring
the mysteries of God's love and all that goes with it ... others
around the nation deny the public importance of the private virtues
you are mastering.''
   Reagan, accompanied by Education Secretary Lauro Cavazos,
visited Archbishop Carroll High School, where students of that
school were gathered in a gymnasium with students from All Saints
High School.
