help parents who wish to send their children to parochial schools.
   ``Catholic schools across America are showing that private
virtue and public interest do indeed live together,'' he said. ``I
know that your parents all make great sacrifices so that you can
come here. ... For years, I have been urging Congress to allow your
parents to support your education either through tuition tax
credits or vouchers.''
   ``We need a Congress that shares and supports the values of the
American people,'' he said.
   Reagan praised the young people for preparing themselves for
leadership positions in the future.
   ``Isn't that because you are not only learning the ABCs but also
about right and wrong, good and evil, and the nature of God's
love?'' he said.
