<HEAD>Wife Of Arms Control Adviser Dead At 70</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mary Rita Rowny, 70, wife of presidential arms
control adviser Edward L. Rowny, died of cancer Sunday at Walter
Reed Army Medical Center. She lived in Arlington, Va.
   During their 47-year marriage, Mrs. Rowny, a native of
Baltimore, accompanied her husband to assignments in Japan, France,
Belgium, Switzerland and West Germany. Survivors include a daughter
and four sons.
</TEXT>
