<HEAD>Cincinnati Post Endorses George Bush</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Political Rdp</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Cincinnati Post endorsed Republican George
Bush for president, praising him in an editorial in its Monday
afternoon editions for his experience in business and government.
   The editorial also called Bush's rival, Democrat Michael S.
Dukakis, ``one of the least prepared candidates for president in
recent years'' whose experience in government is limited to the
Massachussets Statehouse in Boston.
   Bush received endorsements Sunday from three other Ohio
newspapers: The Columbus Dispatch, The Cincinnati Enquirer and The
(Elyria) Chronicle-Telegram. Dukakis has received no Ohio newspaper
endorsements so far.
   The editorial by the Scripps Howard newspaper compared Bush's
resume as a wartime naval flier, businessman, congressman,
Republican national chairman, United Nations ambassador, U.S. envoy
to China and CIA director and said the comparison with Dukakis'
portfolio ``isn't even close.''
