<HEAD>London Share Firmer At Midday On Takeover Bids</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices firmed in London at midday Monday.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was 17.1
points higher, or 0.9 percent, at 1857.7 by 12:17 local time.
   Volume totaled 246.0 million shares, compared with 350 million
shares at the same time Friday.
   Traders said the brewery sector was by far the strongest feature
at midday, drawing support from news that the Australian brewery
Elders IXL Ltd. launched a $2.8 billion bid for Scottish and
Newcastle of Scotland.
   In other takeover news, Associated Newspapers agreed to a $2.1
billion friendly bid from Daily Mail and General Trust.
</TEXT>
