<2ND_LINE>BC-Associated Newspapers,0102</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Investment Company To Buy Rest of Associated Newspapers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Daily Mail and General Trust PLC, a British
investment firm, said Monday that it agreed to acquire the 50.5
percent of Associated Newspapers Holdings PLC it doesn't already
own.
   The $13.46-a-share offer for the remaining 66.9 million shares
outstanding values the printing and publishing company at $2.1
billion.
   Associated Newspapers had pre-tax profit of $100 million on
sales of $1.0 billion in the year ended Sept. 30, 1987. The company
publishes the London newspapers the Daily Mail, Mail on Sunday and
the Evening Standard.
</TEXT>
