<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 2.1 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.797 million tons in
the week ended Oct. 15, a decrease of 2.1 percent from the previous
week's 1.836 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 83.8 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 85.6 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
79.089 million net tons, an increase of 16.5 percent from the
67.885 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.5 percent of capacity,
compared with 76.8 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Oct. 15: Northeast
Coast, 268,000; Pittsburgh, 190,000; Youngstown, 98,000; Lake Erie,
141,000; Detroit, 157,000; Chicago, 439,000; Midwest, 185,000;
Southern, 227,000; and Western, 92,000.
