<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Coke,0220</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Coca-Cola's Profit Up 8.9 Percent in Third Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coca-Cola Co. on Monday reported an increase of
8.9 percent in third-quarter profit from a year earlier, largely
due to an increase in volume.
   The soft drink maker and distributor said its net income in the
third quarter rose to $295.6 million, or 81 cents a share, from
$271.4 million, or 72 cents a share, a year earlier.
   Third-quarter revenue was up 5.7 percent, to $2.1 billion from
$2.0 billion.
   ``The momentum established in the first half of 1988 continued
in the third quarter, reflecting the success of our unit volume
building activities around the world,'' said Chief Executive
Officer Roberto C. Goizueta.
   The company said soft drink and syrup shipments in the third
quarter were up 5 percent in the United States and 7 percent
overseas, with Europe and the Pacific leading the international
markets.
   Soft drink unit volume grew 6 percent worldwide in both the
third quarter and the first nine months of the year, Coca-Cola said.
   For the January-September period, net income rose 11.9 percent _
to $809.2 million, or $2.20 a share, from $723.2 million, or $1.91
a share, a year earlier.
   Nine-month revenue increased 11.4 percent, to $6.3 billion from
$5.7 billion.
</TEXT>
