<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-TRW     10-17 0265</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-TRW,0275</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sale Of Pump, Cable Operations Boost TRW Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   TRW Inc.'s third-quarter earnings increased 7.9
percent to $68 million because of the sale of the company's TRW
Reda Pump and TRW Oilwell Cable operations, the company said Monday.
   TRW's earnings for the third quarter last year were $63 million.
Net earnings per share rose to $1.11, from $1.01 last year.
   Sales totaled $1.65 billion, off 3 percent from $1.70 billion a
year ago.
   The company said its $63 million after-tax gain from the sale of
TRW Reda Pump and TRW Oilwell Cable were partially offset by an
after-tax charge of $43 million to cover the cost of a program to
resolve claims from dealers and truck owners arising from the
recall of integral steering gears for heavy-duty trucks.
   ``Our space and defense business was down somewhat, as expected
given the current market uncertainty and last year's very strong
third quarter,'' said Ruben F. Mettler, chairman and chief
executive officer. ``Without the recall costs, our automotive
business would have posted another good quarter and what has been a
very good year for the segment.''
   Sales in the space and defense segment dropped 5 percent from
$827 million to $786 million. In the automotive segment, TRW said
its third-quarter sales rose 11 percent from $513 million to $679
million. Sales in the information systems segment rose 6 percent
from $128 million to $135 million, the company said.
   For the nine months, the company reported net earnings of $205
million, up from $177 million, and net sales of $5.27 billion, from
$5.08 billion.
</TEXT>
